<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak " data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<p>You can find specific documents for this department using the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=&publication_filter_option=all&topics%5B%5D=all&departments%5B%5D=veterinary-medicines-directorate&official_document_status=all&world_locations%5B%5D=all&from_date=&to_date=">publication search</a>.</p>

<p>If the information you want is not routinely published, you can make a request for it under the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/make-a-freedom-of-information-request">Freedom of Information Act</a>.</p>

<h2 id="who-we-are-and-what-we-do">Who we are and what we do</h2>

<p>Organisational information, location and contacts:</p>

<ul>
  <li>can be found on <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/veterinary-medicines-directorate/about">About us</a>
</li>
</ul>

<p>More information can be found on our <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/veterinary-medicines-directorate">corporate page</a>, such as:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/veterinary-medicines-directorate/about#our-responsibilities">responsibilities</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/veterinary-medicines-directorate/about#service-standards">service standards</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/veterinary-medicines-directorate/about#statement-of-objectivity-and-impartiality">statement of objectivity and impartiality</a></li>
</ul>

<h2 id="what-we-spend-and-how-we-spend-it">What we spend and how we spend it</h2>

<p>Our <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=&publication_filter_option=corporate-reports&topics%5B%5D=all&departments%5B%5D=veterinary-medicines-directorate&official_document_status=all&world_locations%5B%5D=all&from_date=&to_date=">annual report & accounts</a> give details of our financial accounts, which are audited by the National Audit Office.</p>

<h2 id="what-our-priorities-are-and-how-we-are-doing">What our priorities are and how we are doing</h2>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>Departmental strategies can be found in the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/defras-strategy-to-2020-creating-a-great-place-for-living">Defra’s strategy to 2020: creating a great place for living</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><span id="attachment_2228291" class="attachment-inline">
<a href="/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/554186/_313751_VMD_Published_Standards.pdf">VMD published standards</a>
(<span class="type"><abbr title="Portable Document Format">PDF</abbr></span>, <span class="file-size">283KB</span>, <span class="page-length">8 pages</span>)
</span>
 covers our performance indicators and assessment</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/veterinary-medicines-directorate/about#published-standards">VMD Deliverables and KPIs</a></p>
  </li>
</ul>

<h2 id="how-we-make-decisions">How we make decisions</h2>

<p>We don’t publish details of our decision-making processes and records of our decisions but you can request them from <a href="mailto:postmaster@vmd.defra.gsi.gov.uk">postmaster@vmd.defra.gsi.gov.uk</a>.</p>

<h2 id="other-information">Other information</h2>

<p>Data sets such as the VMD’s organogram of staff roles & salary data can be found on <a rel="external" href="https://data.gov.uk/publisher/veterinary-medicines-directorate">Data.gov.uk</a></p>

